    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "unibilium is licensed as LGPL 3, and such a license prevents certain types of deployment of neovim at large corporations which take license compliance very seriously.  I came to write this feature request not out of whim, but as a response to a hurdle that I and others are facing.\r\n\r\nI have not done a thorough review of all the third party dependencies, but AFAIK this is the only LGPL 3 blocker.  \r\n\r\nReplacing unibilium will increase adoption of neovim tremendously.\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2025-01-11T15:23:44Z",
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Only the _new_ code developed for nvim has been submitted under the Apache license.  All of the original Vim code is still licensed under its GPL-like (or more likely, according to II.2.e., GPL-2+) license.\r\n\r\nGiven that, I find it hard to believe that unibilium's LGPL-3 license is the limiting factor here, if your reviewers are doing their due diligence.",
