            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "GPL v2 has a very different hurdle for approval than GPL v3, because it is a different license with different terms and conditions, and GPLv3 is absolutely a limiting factor in this case.  Your comment suggests the people who are setting or enforcing policy may be uninformed or sloppy.  I am not at all offended by this suggestion as it seems like a natural hypothesis to propose given all the general incompetence in the world.  However, please accept my explanation that this is not the case; the people who make these decisions are qualified and principled.\r\n\r\nAlso, I do not know of any (L)GPL v3 code in the dependencies of vim 8.x which I took a quick glance at.  Notably, I find no reference to unibilium in that code base.",
