        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> I don't know where you got that idea from.\n\nBased on the fact that this issue to remove the Unibilium dependency remains open, and [this comment](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/21832#discussion_r1071143289) from @justinmk which links to this issue which says what it will be replaced with:\n\n> ...that issue is parked until we can replace unibilium with https://github.com/leonerd/libtickit\n\nPerhaps that comment is outdated based on the current direction the core team is headed. I only know what is publicly available. It wasn't my intention to speak for anyone else.\n\n>  We have zero intention of doing that.\n\nLeaving this issue open as it is now makes it seem like there is some non-zero amount of intention of doing that. If there is no intention to remove the dependency, I suggest this issue be closed with a comment to indicate that intention, or that this issue be converted into a discussion to indicate that is in, in fact, just a discussion and not an issue that is meant to be addressed. \n\nA closed issue can always be re-opened later if people's minds change. Leaving it open makes it seem like it is meant to be addressed at some point.",
